The following are major news items in leading Pakistani
English newspapers Wednesday. The News: -- Two powerful bombs rocked
the violent port city of Karachi Tuesday injuring at least 21 people,
say police officials on the scene. The Nation: -- Pakistan inches
towards default on its 32 billion U.S. dollar foreign debt repayments
as foreign exchange reserves fell to 453 million dollars Tuesday with
no sign of an early bailout package from the International Monetary
Fund. The Frontier Post -- Pakistan and Saudi Arabia have agreed on the
formation of a joint business council in the private sector to boost
interaction for tapping their trade and investment potential. The
Muslim -- Afghanistan's Taliban and the opposition alliance have agreed
on a week-long ceasefire to allow them to start negotiations, an aide
to opposition commander Ahmed Shah Masud said Tuesday.
